      • setView

        public static <E> ArrayBackedSet<E> setView(java.util.List<E> list)
        Return a Set implementation backed by the supplied List. The implementation assumes that elements in the list are unique. The resulting view is serializable.
        Type Parameters:
        E - the type of elements in the set
        Parameters:
        list - the list to be viewed as if it was a set
        Returns:
        a Set backed by the supplied list

        Type Parameters:

        Parameters:
        coll - the set to be viewed as if it was a list
        Returns:

      • mapKeyIndexer

        public static <K> java.util.function.IntFunction<K> mapKeyIndexer(ArrayBackedMap<K,?> map)
        Returns a functional instance for mapping indexes onto keys of the supplied ArrayBackedMap. The instance is serializable, to allow map views to be serialized.
        Type Parameters:
        K - the key type
        Parameters:
        map - the array-backed map from which keys will be indexed
        Returns:
        an IntFunction suitable for passing to an ArrayBackedImmutableList
